- "gardeners" refers to the developers;
- "nurtured" refers to the commits made;
- "most impactful and intricate bug fixes" refers to the top 3 bug fix commits based on the number of developers involved and the exponential complexity;
- "more than one" means the project has more than one such top commit.

- 'My Project' refers to a specific project in the database;
- 'Bloom' and 'flower' are metaphors for commits in the project;
- 'Type of bloom' refers to the classification of the commit (e.g., bug fix, new feature, documentation update);
- 'Complexity' is measured by the exponential complexity of the commit.

